last_episode_to_air.overview: Not many can intimidate North America’s top predator, T. rex, whose size and bite are a deadly combo—except for a giant winged foe.

name: Prehistoric Planet
overview: Experience the wonders of our world like never before in this epic docuseries from Jon Favreau and the producers of Planet Earth. Travel back 66 million years to when majestic dinosaurs and extraordinary creatures roamed the lands, seas, and skies.

episodes.name: Coasts
episodes.overview: A pregnant Tuarangisaurus is in distress—and her young calf can sense it—as she travels waters that are home to the ocean’s deadliest predators.

episodes.name: Deserts
episodes.overview: Above the deserts of North Africa, aerial combat ensues as male Barbaridactylus pterosaurs fight for the attention of females below.

episodes.name: Freshwater
episodes.overview: With its feathered body and duck bill, the eight-ton Deinocheirus wades through an Asian wetland in search of relief from pesky biting flies.

episodes.name: Ice Worlds
episodes.overview: Within the snow-covered forest, a tense standoff develops between ancient rivals, Pachyrhinosaurus and Nanuqsaurus.

episodes.name: Forests
episodes.overview: A journey through an underground cave in North America turns perilous when a young Triceratops is separated from its mother.

episodes.name: Islands
episodes.overview: On a small island, a monumental display takes place as the giant Hatzegopteryx reveals his gentler side to woo a mate.

episodes.name: Badlands
episodes.overview: Trudging through a scorching desert, two young Tarchia find relief at an oasis and encounter an adult twice their size, ready to lay claim.

episodes.name: Swamps
episodes.overview: In a drought-stricken basin where much has perished, an old Pachycephalosaurus bull defends his leadership against a young challenger.

episodes.name: Oceans
episodes.overview: Deep beneath the water’s surface, the world’s largest predator—the Mosasaurus—lies in wait to ambush unsuspecting prey.
